Such a statement this week was circulated by volunteers of the "My Sea" campaign.
For the fifth year, walking along the Gulf of Riga, the activists have concluded that the number of waste left by the population has increased every hundred meters.
Unfortunately, this year's critical assessment has come in.
"We see that this will be the year when the number of waste per 100 meters on the beach can even exceed 200 units," says Jānis Ulme, a spokesman for the expedition "My Sea".
