"Latvenergo" follows the process of opening the gas market also from the position of a potential trader.
The state energy company "Latvenergo" follows the process of opening the gas market both from the position of the consumer and the potential trader, said the company's spokeswoman Ivita Bidere.
"The decision on whether Latvenergo will join the gas market in the future as a trader will be determined by what gas market model and legal framework will be established."
"Therefore, for our part, we are actively involved in the establishment and commenting of laws and regulations, as well as submit our proposals," Bidere said.
The agency BNS has already written that the Ministry of Economics (ME) in cooperation with the Public Utilities Commission and the energy company "Latvijas Gāze" has developed the Cabinet of Ministers Regulations Project "Regulations on Trade and Use of Natural Gas" which will change the existing principles of natural gas market operation, ensuring the right to freely choose a natural gas trader for natural gas users as of 3 April 2017.
Working on the new regulation of the natural gas market, the aim of the EM is to make the natural gas trade process as simple as possible and understandable to the user.
Therefore, as the most effective and convenient service solution for the user, the "centric model of the trader" has been chosen, in which all activities related to customer service are provided by the trader - one contract, one invoice and one place for the provision of information and customer service, leaving the technical issues of the natural gas distribution system to the operator of the distribution system.
A similar solution is currently being implemented in electricity trading.
We remind that household users are expected to start the market - even after 3 April 2017, those household users who will not wish to choose another natural gas trader will be able to continue receiving natural gas from the existing trader at a regulated price, thus becoming related users.
"In this case, the obligation to supply natural gas to related users at a regulated price is imposed on the public trader," the ministry informed.
In turn, merchants will have to choose a natural gas trader with which to enter into a natural gas trade contract.
Until the conclusion of a natural gas trade agreement, natural gas trade will be ensured by the current natural gas trader for a certain period of time for a certain period of time.
The draft Cabinet Regulations defines in detail the rights and obligations of a natural gas trader, system operator and users.
This Regulation prescribes the procedures by which natural gas shall be supplied to users and discontinue the supply thereof, the requirements for the safe use of the natural gas system, the rights of the trader, the public trader, the system operator, the user and the owner of the gasified object in the supply and use of natural gas; the procedures by which the settlements for the services received, the amount of late payment interest, the procedures for changing traders and the supply of customers in the event of natural gas supply disruptions; the procedures by which the public trader shall ensure the supply of natural gas to the related users.
