The turnover of the canned food producer "Zilā lagūna" last year shrank by 33.8%.
The turnover of the canned food producer "Zilā lagūna" last year was 4.202 million euros, which is 33.8% less than a year ago, while the company's losses decreased 5.7 times - to 904.7 thousand euros, according to the annual financial report published in the database "Lursoft".
According to the company’s management report, in 2015 the company was operating at a loss due to several reasons, including due to the constant lack of working capital caused by the departure of Unicredit Bank from the Baltic market, interrupting the previously existing credit line, and leaving the "Zilo lagūna" with concluded contracts without the possibility to execute them.
Consequently, the company did not have sufficient funds to buy cheaper raw materials in large volumes and receive a volume discount.
The departure of the bank from the Latvian market also prevented the company from implementing the European Union Structural Funds support projects, which would have allowed the plant to purchase new production equipment and modernize the infrastructure.
Similarly, the company’s financial indicators in the last year were negatively affected by the rise in raw material prices and the unwillingness of customers to pay more than the company’s manufactured goods.
"Only in the second half of July 2016 customers recognized price changes and were ready to buy goods at the new - highest - prices", says the company's management.
Also in 2015, "Zilā lagūna" started negotiations with potential investors, including the valuation of the company's movable and real estate.
Investors have already been to the company's largest creditor Unicredit Leasing, where the parties have got to know and discussed possible investment plans.
At the same time, the company’s activities and development were positively influenced by the implementation of the restructuring and optimization plan started in 2014 and 2015.
This plan included the improvement and optimisation of technological processes, which allows to achieve greater productivity and capacity of production.
"A number of equipment were purchased that provide a higher production rate," the company's management said.
The management of "Blue Lagoon" notes that the purchased equipment in 2016 will allow the company's production unit to fulfill such orders that were not possible so far.
The first batch of production, which will be produced on this equipment, will be ready in August.
As the intent protocols on the sale of the product has already been signed, all produced will be sold according to the letter of intent.
The new product will increase its turnover by about 300 thousand euros per month", says the company's management.
The company also plans to sign a cooperation agreement on the supply of fish products to Iraq in August 2016.
In 2016, "Blue Lagoon" has sent the first experimental container to Israel, expanded the outlet to Cyprus and this year will sign a cooperation agreement with a new supermarket chain in the US in September.
As a result of all the above measures, the company plans to increase its turnover.
In 2014, "Zila lagūna" worked with a turnover of 6.347 million euros and a loss of 5.113 million euros.
"Zilā lagūna" was founded in 1997 and its share capital is 1.156 million euros.
The company is owned by two Latvian individuals - Mikhail Kaidanov (89,11%) and Igors Širšons (10.89%).
